        public static ETPush getInstance()
                          throws ETException
        Primary accessor for the ETPush singleton. All Push interactions with ExactTarget should take place through this method. Before using this method, you must first call readyAimFire(Application, String, String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean, boolean) from your Application's Application.onCreate() method.

      • readyAimFire

        public static void readyAimFire(ETPushConfig pushConfig)
                         throws ETException
        Call this from your Application's Application.onCreate() method. This initializes ETPush.

        Configures the SDK to point to the correct Code@ application.

        These credentials are provided by Code@ExactTarget, and are generated there. Best practice is to create two applications, one for a dev instance, and one for prod.

        Parameters:
        pushConfig - ETPushConfig
        Throws:
        ETException

      • readyAimFire

        @Deprecated
public static void readyAimFire(android.app.Application applicationContext,
                           String etAppId,
                           String accessToken,
                           String gcmSenderId,
                           boolean enableETanalytics,
                           boolean enableLocationManager,
                           boolean enableCloudPages)
                         throws ETException
        Deprecated. use readyAimFire(ETPushConfig) or readyAimFire(Application, String, String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean, boolean) instead
        Call this from your Application's Application.onCreate() method. This initializes ETPush.

        Configures the SDK to point to the correct Code@ application.

        These credentials are provided by Code@ExactTarget, and are generated there. Best practice is to create two applications, one for a dev instance, and one for prod.

        Parameters:
        applicationContext - Must be an application getContext. Do not send Activity getContext.
        etAppId - Generated application ID to identify with ExactTarget
        accessToken - Generated token to allow access to the Fuel API
        gcmSenderId - The GCM project ID from your Google Cloud Messaging account
        enableETanalytics - true to activate Salesforce Marketing Cloud Analytics. You must have use activityResumed() and activityPaused() from ETPush in each of your activities onPause() and onResume() methods
        enableLocationManager - true if the location manager or geofencing will be used
        enableCloudPages - true if CloudPage Inbox will be used
        Throws:
        ETException

      • readyAimFire

        public static void readyAimFire(android.app.Application inApplicationContext,
                String inEtAppId,
                String inAccessToken,
                String inGcmSenderId,
                boolean inEnableETanalytics,
                boolean inEnablePIanalytics,
                boolean inEnableLocationManager,
                boolean inEnableCloudPages)
                         throws ETException
        Call this from your Application's Application.onCreate() method. This initializes ETPush.

        This method allows you to also add Web and Mobile Analytics to your app. See Code@ doc for more info.

        Configures the SDK to point to the correct Code@ application.

        These credentials are provided by Code@ExactTarget, and are generated there. Best practice is to create two applications, one for a dev instance, and one for prod.

        Parameters:
        inApplicationContext - Must be an application getContext. Do not send Activity getContext.
        inEtAppId - Generated application ID to identify with ExactTarget
        inAccessToken - Generated token to allow access to the Fuel API
        inEnableETanalytics - true to activate Salesforce Marketing Cloud Analytics. You must have use activityResumed() and activityPaused() from ETPush in each of your activities onPause() and onResume() methods
        inEnablePIanalytics - true to activate Web and Mobile Analytics. You must have use activityResumed() and activityPaused() from ETPush in each of your activities onPause() and onResume() methods
        inEnableLocationManager - true if the location manager or geofencing will be used
        inEnableCloudPages - true if CloudPage Inbox will be used
        Throws:
        ETException

      • isPushEnabled

        public boolean isPushEnabled()
        Checks persistent preferences for the state of Push. Push is enabled by either enablePush() or disablePush(), and the SDK ships with Push disabled by default. Best practice dictates that the user gathers opt-in and explicitly enables Push.
        Returns:
        boolean The state of push, either on or off, as managed by the Push Manager.

      • enablePush

        public void enablePush()
                throws ETException
        Enables push and push accessories in the SDK.

        This method should be called when explicit permission for Push has been given by the user. No interface for this is provided. By comparison, iOS will prompt the user when an app wants to send Push notifications. As Android doesn't, you must do so on your own.

        Throws:
        ETException
        See Also:
        disablePush()

      • thirdPartyPushServicesAvailable

                                           throws ETException
        Throws:
        ETException

      • disablePush

        public void disablePush()
                 throws ETException
        Disables push and push accessories in the SDK.

        This method should be called if the user decided they no longer wish to receive Push notifications. To be compliant, you need to provide the user with means to disable Push.

        If googleplayservices library is outdated, a notification is displayed to prompt the user to install it.

        Throws:
        ETException
        See Also:
        enablePush()

      • addAttribute

        public void addAttribute(String attribute,
                String value)
                  throws ETException
        Adds an attribute to current user's Contact model.

        This data is available in MobilePush, and will automatically map to any matching attribute within MobilePush/Contacts.

        Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided.

        Parameters:
        attribute - Attribute name
        value - Value to assign to that attribute for this user
        Throws:
        ETException

      • removeAttribute

        public void removeAttribute(String attribute)
                     throws ETException
        Removes an attribute from the current user's data, and prevents it from being sent to ExactTarget. This will also cause that attribute to be cleared in Contacts.

        Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided.

        Parameters:
        attribute - Name of the attribute to remove.
        Throws:
        ETException
